title: Professional Woman In Her Thirties Gains The Clarity To Continue Working On Her Side Business
description: In this episode, we sit down with Maria, a professional woman in her early 30s, and help her feel less helpless with starting her own creative business selling mugs - while juggling a full time job, nurturing her relationship with her husband, starting a family, and moving to a new country.
author: Conrad Lin

title: Understanding Dating and Romantic Relationships From Different Perspectives
description: In this episode, we breakdown dating and romantic relationships, and how to understand it from different perspectives as described in the Better Life Framework by the Co-x3 Family Foundation. This episode will help anyone struggling with dating in the modern world.
author: Co-x3 Family Foundation

title: Understanding Relationships With Your Parents As Adults From Different Perspectives
description: In this episode, we breakdown our relationships with our parents as adults, and how to understand them from different perspectives as described in the Better Life Framework by the Co-x3 Family Foundation. This episode will help anyone struggling with managing their relationship with parents and their expectations.
author: Co-x3 Family Foundation

title: 27 Year Old Woman Working In Big Tech Discovers Her Path To Self-Alignment and Breaking Through
description: In this episode, we sit down with Sarah, a 27 year old woman working in a big tech company and discuss how to live a life that is aligned with her true self. She also explores how to work on her side hustle by time-blocking her calendar to make time, using our Notion templates to keep projects organized, and bringing her finish line closer.
author: Conrad Lin

title: Understanding Relationships With Our Children From Different Perspectives
description: In this episode, we breakdown the relationships we have with our children and how to understand them from different perspectives as described in the Better Life Framework by the Co-x3 Family Foundation. This episode will help anyone struggling with connecting with their children and make them feel valued.
author: Co-x3 Family Foundation

title: Entrepreneur In His 40s Discovers What Happiness Is To Him And How To Balance Work and Life
description: In this episode, we sit down with Stefan, a seasoned entrepreneur in his 40s and discuss what happiness is and how to be our best selves.
author: Conrad Lin
